<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section version="5.0"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd"
         xml:id="gui.animation_toolbar" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"
         xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
         xmlns:ns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <title>Animation toolbar</title>

  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/goto_first.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Go to first frame</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Jumps to the first frame of the animation sequence.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/goto_last.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Go to last frame</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Jumps to the last frame of the animation sequence.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/goto_previous_frame.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Go to previous frame</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Steps one frame back in the animation sequence.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/goto_next_frame.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Go to next frame</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Steps one frame forward in the animation sequence.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/play_animation.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Play Animation</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Starts/stops playing the animation in the viewports.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/animation_mode.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Animation Mode</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Enables/disables animation mode. Changing a numerical parameter
        or the position of some object in the scene while the animation mode
        is active will generate an animation keyframe. A red animation time
        slider and a red viewport border indicate that animation mode is
        active.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/animation_settings.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Animation Settings</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opens the <link
        linkend="gui.animation_settings_dialog">Animation Settings Dialog
        box</link>.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><inlinemediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_toolbar/current_animation_frame.png"
                       format="PNG" valign="top" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject> Current Animation Frame</term>

      <listitem>
        <para>Numerical input box that controls the current animation
        position. It is meant as an alternative way of jumping to a certain
        animation time in addition to the Animation Time Slider.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

  <section>
    <title>Animation time slider</title>

    <para>The animation time slider is located below the <link
    linkend="gui.viewports_area">viewports area</link>. It can be dragged with
    the mouse to navigate in time.</para>
  </section>

  <section xml:id="gui.animation_settings_dialog">
    <title>Animation settings dialog</title>

    <figure>
      <title>Animation settings dialog</title>

      <screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/animation_settings_dialog/dialog_screenshot.png"
                       format="PNG" xml:base="../../../"/>
          </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot>
    </figure>

    <para>This dialog lets the user setup the animation for the current scene.
    The animation speed is given as frames per second and can only be changed
    in discrete steps because OVITO internally works with a time unit called
    <firstterm>time ticks</firstterm>. One time tick is 1/4800 of a second,
    allowing only integer divisors of 4800 for the frames per second
    value.</para>

    <para>The duration of the animation is defined by the start frame number
    and the end frame number. The number of animation frames is given by the
    formula (end â€“ start + 1).</para>

    <para>Changing the frames per second value will automatically alter the
    number of animation frames to keep the animation length (in seconds)
    constant. It will also rescale the positions of all animation keys in the
    scene to preserve their timing.</para>

    <para>To just change the playback speed for the animation in the viewports
    without touching the animation keys and the animation interval, the
    playback speed multiplier can be set in the dialog.</para>
  </section>
</section>
